# scRNA-seq Cell Type Benchmark

A production-quality computational biology framework for benchmarking machine learning methods for automated cell type annotation from single-cell RNA sequencing data.

---

## Project Goals

This repository benchmarks classical machine learning and modern computational biology methods across public scRNA-seq datasets while emphasizing reproducible software engineering.

Current focus includes

- Logistic Regression
- Random Forest
- Multi-layer Perceptron
- XGBoost
- CellTypist
- scPred

Future versions will include transformer-based foundation models.

---

